# UI/UX Hard Lock Policy — Zero Tolerance

## Protected Files (DO NOT MODIFY unless explicitly approved)

- `app.js`
- `index.html`
- `styles.css`
- `src/lib/ai/index.js`

## Protected Behavior (DO NOT break or modify casually)

- Visible buttons
- Click behavior (event delegation via `data-action`)
- Auth screen flow
- Questionnaire flow
- Dashboard flow
- Render/init order
- Navigation/view switching
- Loading overlays / modal blocking behavior
- Session restore order (affects clickability)

## Allowed Files by Default

Modify ONLY when the task truly requires it and does NOT affect protected UI:

- `src/lib/ai/*` (except `index.js`)
- `src/lib/core/*`
- `src/lib/data/*`

## Mandatory Pre-Check (before any changes)

1. List files to be modified
2. If any protected file is included → STOP and explain why it is required
3. If a feature can be implemented without touching protected files → DO NOT TOUCH THEM

## Mandatory Post-Check (after changes)

Verify all of the following:

1. Landing/auth buttons visible
2. Buttons clickable
3. Questionnaire works
4. Generate/Create Plan works
5. Dashboard renders
6. Logout works
7. No overlay blocks clicks
8. No blank sections appear

## Rule

If a change risks the UI shell → STOP and ask for explicit UI-core approval.
